table.name: ob_order_base
table.description: This is the base table that defines the orders. An order base can have multiple origins, destinations, different times etc. Multiple order releases can be created against one order base. In the XML side, the TransOrder(Transportation Order) is similar to Order base.

columns.name: ORDER_BASE_GID
columns.description: The GID for the order base.

columns.name: ORDER_BASE_XID
columns.description: The XID for the order base.

columns.name: EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_ID
columns.description: The identifier for the external system that provided the base order. For example a user's Oracle or other ERP system could be providing the order IDs.

columns.name: PAYMENT_METHOD_CODE_GID
columns.description: The payment method GID contains the GID for the payment method code for the order. Examples of payment method include electronic fund transfer and cash on delivery.

columns.name: INCO_TERM_GID
columns.description: The INCO term GID contains the GID for the incoterms associated with the order base.

columns.name: TERM_LOCATION_TEXT
columns.description: The term location text contains additional information related to the incoterms for the order.

columns.name: PLANNING_GROUP_GID
columns.description: The planning group GID used to group orders into different bulk planning waves.

columns.name: FIXED_ITINERARY_GID
columns.description: The fixed buy side itinerary GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained itinerary. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: ORDER_TYPE_GID
columns.description: The order type GID contains the unique identifier for the order type. Examples of order types include: CUSTOMER_ORDERS INTERFACILITY RETURNS INTEGRATION WEB

columns.name: TIME_WINDOW_EMPHASIS_GID
columns.description: The time window emphasis GID contains the unique identifier to tell the planning engine whether early or late (or both) pickup and delivery times are important when creating a shipment.

columns.name: RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The buy rate service profile GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate service profile. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: SERVPROV_GID
columns.description: The buy service provider GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained service provider. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: SERVPROV_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The buy service provider profile GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained  service provider profile. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: The buy transport mode GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained  transport mode. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: MODE_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The buy mode profile GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained  transport mode profile. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_GROUP_GID
columns.description: The buy equipment group GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained equipment group. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_GROUP_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The buy equipment group profile GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained equipment group profile. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: PROCESSING_CODE_GID
columns.description: A unique pointer to define the processing codes in the system. The system has only one processing code, 'PLN', which means to plan the shipment from the order release.

columns.name: SHIP_WITH_GROUP
columns.description: Currently not supported. Ship with group is on the order base ship unit and order base line level.

columns.name: EFFECTIVE_DATE
columns.description: Effective date of the order.

columns.name: EXPIRATION_DATE
columns.description: The expiration date of the order.

columns.name: CR_TS
columns.description: A timestamp for order base processing.

columns.name: IS_TEMPLATE
columns.description: A Y/N flag to identify if this order is just a template and order base (s) can be created out of it.

columns.name: RATE_OFFERING_GID
columns.description: The buy rate offering GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate offering. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: RATE_GEO_GID
columns.description: The buy rate geography details GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate detail. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: SELL_RATE_OFFERING_GID
columns.description: The sell rate offering GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate offering. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: SELL_RATE_GEO_GID
columns.description: The sell rate geography details GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate detail. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: FIXED_SELL_ITINERARY_GID
columns.description: The fixed buy side itinerary GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained itinerary This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT
columns.description: The total gross weight calculated from the order base lines.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total gross weight unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The total gross weight in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME
columns.description: The total gross volume calculated from the order base lines.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total gross volume unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The total gross volume in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: MUST_SHIP_DIRECT
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order release must ship direct.

columns.name: MUST_SHIP_THRU_X_DOCK
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order release must ship through cross dock.

columns.name: MUST_SHIP_THRU_POOL
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order release must ship through pool.

columns.name: INDICATOR
columns.description: An indicator field that can be set to display important information about the order base.

columns.name: IS_KNOWN_SHIPPER
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether the shipper involved party is a known shipper for air travel.

columns.name: RELEASE_METHOD_GID
columns.description: The release method GID is the order configuration rule and this drives the configuration of the order such as ship unit or line as well as various calculations.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_WEIGHT
columns.description: The total net weight calculated from the order release lines.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total net weight unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The total net weight in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_VOLUME
columns.description: The total net volume calculated from the order release lines.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total net volume unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_NET_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The total net volume in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: DIM_RATE_FACTOR_GID
columns.description: The dim factor to be used when allocating by dimensional weight for a business unit and rate calculations.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED1_ICON_GID
columns.description: Can store a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes of the order base.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED2_ICON_GID
columns.description: Can store a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes of the order base.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED3_ICON_GID
columns.description: Can store a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes of the order base.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED4_ICON_GID
columns.description: Can store a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes of the order base.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED5_ICON_GID
columns.description: Can store a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes of the order base.

columns.name: BUNDLING_TYPE
columns.description: The bundling type is automatic or manual only allow bundling; they are distinguished only by user defined queries.  Bundling type of do not bundle means order will never be bundled with other orders.

columns.name: TOTAL_DECLARED_VALUE
columns.description: The total declared value calculated from the order base lines.

columns.name: TOTAL_DECLARED_VALUE_GID
columns.description: The total declared value currency identifier.

columns.name: TOTAL_DECLARED_VALUE_BASE
columns.description: The total declared value in the base currency.

columns.name: SELL_SERVPROV_GID
columns.description: The sell service provider GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained service provider. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: SELL_SERVPROV_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The sell service provider profile GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained service provider profile. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: RATE_SERVICE_GID
columns.description: The buy rate service GID can be defined to force the order release to be schedule with a constrained rate service. This value is copied to any associated order releases.

columns.name: DEFAULT_STOWAGE_MODE_GID
columns.description: The default stowage mode to use for this order when loading onto stowage consol shipments.

columns.name: STUFF_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The location for stuffing (loading) the container prior to shipping.

columns.name: DESTUFF_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The location for destuffing (unloading) the container after the ocean move.

columns.name: CUSTOMER_UNITIZATION_REQUEST
columns.description: The customer's request for unitization location.

columns.name: UNITIZATION_CONDITION_NAME
columns.description: The unitization (loading of equipment) condition name value.

columns.name: IS_IGNORE_LOCATION_CALENDAR
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether to ignore the source and destination calendar when planning the order.

columns.name: PICKUP_ROUTING_SEQUENCE_GID
columns.description: The pickup location routing sequence that controls how the stops can be planned for pickup such as first, absolute first, last.

columns.name: DROPOFF_ROUTING_SEQUENCE_GID
columns.description: The dropoff location routing sequence that controls how the stops can be planned for pickup such as first, absolute first, last.

columns.name: PRIORITY
columns.description: The priority value assigned to the order base.

columns.name: MARKED_FOR_PURGE
columns.description: A Y/N indicator field, when it is set to 'Y', this row and its child data will be purged.

columns.name: DOMAIN_NAME
columns.description: Database domain where this data is stored.

columns.name: INSERT_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data insert user.

columns.name: INSERT_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of data insert.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data update user.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of the most recent data update.
